==English==
===Etymology===
From the radio show [[Wikipedia:Fibber McGee and Molly#The Closet|Fibber McGee and Molly]], where the door to an overstuffed closet would be opened, and the contents would spill out.
===Noun phrase===
'''Fibber McGee's closet'''
#(''US'') [[household]] [[clutter]]; especially a messy area or room.
#:''This room is like '''Fibber McGee's closet'''; clean it up!''